@krixano have you considered simply not changing license?
for more info on what this would cause, see [here](https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/ZeroNet/issues/2272#issuecomment-549192208)
there are various big projects already doing similar, like the [FFMPEG](https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg/blob/master/LICENSE.md#incompatible-libraries) media processing tool / converter or the [Spigot](https://www.spigotmc.org/threads/buildtools-updates-information.42865/) serverside modding API for Minecraft
